{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 09:36:36.095692", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope\\n- Topology: 1 super-spine (AS 65000), 2 spines (AS 65100/65101), 2 leaves (AS 65200/65201), 2 hosts (pc_0_0 on leaf_router_0_0, pc_0_1 on leaf_router_0_1)\\n- Routing: EBGP throughout, interconnects on 172.16.0.0/16 /31s, host subnets 10.0.0.0/24 (pc_0_0) and 10.0.1.0/24 (pc_0_1)\\n\\n1) Network Health Assessment (Control Plane)\\n- All EBGP sessions are established and stable:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0: Peers 172.16.0.4 (AS 65100), 172.16.0.8 (AS 65101), PfxRcd=1 from each.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1: Peers 172.16.0.6 (AS 65100), 172.16.0.10 (AS 65101), PfxRcd=1 from each.\\n  - spine_router_0_0 and spine_router_0_1: Established with both leaves and the super-spine; PfxRcd shows both /24s from leaves as expected.\\n  - super_spine_router_0: Established with both spines; learns both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24.\\n- RIB/FIB correctness:\\n  - Leaves each have their local /24 connected and learn the other /24 via a spine next-hop.\\n  - Spines have BGP routes to both /24s via leaves.\\n  - Super-spine has BGP to both /24s via a spine.\\nConclusion: Control plane and routing propagation across the Clos fabric are healthy and consistent.\\n\\n2) Data Plane and Host Edge Observations\\n- Host pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2):\\n  - Has default route via 10.0.1.1.\\n  - Can ping its gateway 10.0.1.1 with 0% loss.\\n- Host pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2):\\n  - Initially showed eth0 UP in one snapshot, but later ifconfig reports flags=4098 (not UP/RUNNING). ethtool reports Link detected: no on eth0.\\n  - ip route shows only 10.0.0.0/24 on-link (no default route).\\n  - Ping from pc_0_0 to 10.0.0.1 fails with “Network is unreachable” (indicates the kernel considered the route/interface unusable at that time).\\n  - Leaf to host test: leaf_router_0_0 can ping 10.0.0.2 with 33% packet loss, indicating intermittent connectivity at the access link. ARP entries exist on both ends (pc_0_0 shows 10.0.0.1 REACHABLE; leaf shows 10.0.0.2 seen).\\n- Inter-host reachability:\\n  - pc_0_1 -> pc_0_0 timed out.\\n  - pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1 immediately fails (no default route for off-subnet reply, and primary interface/link issues).\\n\\n3) Anomalies Detected\\n- pc_0_0 access link anomaly:\\n  - ethtool on pc_0_0 eth0: Link detected: no.\\n  - ifconfig later shows eth0 not UP/RUNNING.\\n  - Leaf -> pc_0_0 ping shows packet loss (33%), consistent with an unstable L2/L1 link or host NIC issues.\\n- Host routing asymmetry:\\n  - pc_0_1 has a default route; pc_0_0 does not. This would prevent pc_0_0 from replying to off-subnet traffic even if the link were functioning.\\n\\n4) Fault Localization\\n- Fabric (leaves, spines, super-spine) control plane and routing tables are normal.\\n- The fault is localized to the host edge on the 10.0.0.0/24 side:\\n  - pc_0_0 eth0 and/or its connection to leaf_router_0_0 eth2.\\n\\n5) Probable Root Cause\\n- Primary: pc_0_0’s NIC eth0 is down or flapping (no carrier per ethtool; inconsistent interface state; observed packet loss to the host), causing “Network is unreachable” to its on-link gateway and preventing reliable L2 communication.\\n- Secondary (configuration): pc_0_0 lacks a default route, which would block return traffic to off-subnet destinations (e.g., 10.0.1.2) even if the link were up.\\n\\n6) Impact Summary\\n- Intra-fabric routing is healthy.\\n- End-to-end connectivity between pc_0_1 and pc_0_0 is broken due to the pc_0_0 access link state and missing default route.\\n- pc_0_1’s local connectivity is unaffected; pc_0_0’s local gateway connectivity is intermittently or completely broken depending on the link state at the moment., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='d94e17f2-8550-4844-b106-9154b8ae3b61'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
